* Calculate Places: Clears result fields and recalculates all places.
*   When to use:    After all runners have finished, or whenever results need to be recalculated.
*   How to use:     Double-click to clear and recalculate all place fields.
*   Note:           This clears and recalculates: TIME, PLACE, PACE, DIVPLACE, DIVTOTAL,
*                   SEXPLACE, SEXTOTAL, AGEPLACE, AGETOTAL, RUNNER STATUS.
*   Pace note:      Adding 'K' after a distance converts km to miles for pace.
*                   To get pace per km instead, omit the 'K' (e.g., use '20' not '20K').

* Step 1: Clear all result fields
clear-f.rsm         TIME
clear-f.rsm         NETTIME
clear-f.rsm         PLACE
clear-f.rsm         PACE
clear-f.rsm         DIVPLACE
clear-f.rsm         DIVTOTAL
clear-f.rsm         SEXPLACE
clear-f.rsm         SEXTOTAL
clear-f.rsm         AGEPLACE
clear-f.rsm         AGETOTAL
clear-f.rsm         "RUNNER STATUS"

* Step 2: Compute times, places, and divisions
CalcPlaces.rsm      5K

* Examples for other distances:
* CalcPlaces.rsm    10K
* CalcPlaces.rsm    Half
* CalcPlaces.rsm    20        (pace per km, no 'K' suffix)